                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="162457" author="pjones" created="Thu, 18 Aug 2016 21:32:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So this is confirmed as a duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8091&quot; title=&quot;server_lsi2mti() should return error when fail to get nid&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-8091&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-8091&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="160287" author="hongchao.zhang" created="Fri, 29 Jul 2016 11:03:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;the patch &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/19933/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/19933/&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8091&quot; title=&quot;server_lsi2mti() should return error when fail to get nid&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-8091&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-8091&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; can fix the problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="158984" author="ghagensen" created="Fri, 15 Jul 2016 17:41:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The bad servicenode argument I used was the node&apos;s management interface @ tcp0 . So it was a valid IP, but not a valid NID as it is not on an LNET. The LNET interface was the IB interface. So I assume to reproduce all you would need is a system (or VMs) with 2 interfaces on the HA pair, one for management, one for LNET and define the service nodes to be on the non-lnet interface.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="158977" author="adilger" created="Fri, 15 Jul 2016 17:25:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Gary, can you please provide more details about how the NID was incorrect, so that this can be debugged/fixed properly and there can be a test case added for this.  As it is, I have no idea how to reproduce this problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    </comments>
